Eight people died on Tuesday evening in an accident involving a matatu belonging Central Liners Sacco on the Nyahururu-Nyeri road. The crash occurred at Equator between 6:30pm and 7pm. The victims are from Kiboya village, Ndaragwa. Nyandarua Majority leader and Pondo MCA Kamau Gathungu, Ndaragwa MP Jeremiah Kioni and Kiriita MCA Justus Gaita helped in the rescue efforts. Speaking to the Star on the phone Gathungu said the matatu that was coming from Mukuruwe-ini rolled. Residents had accompanied one of the villagers for the burial of his mother.  Four people died while being treated at Nyahururu Referral Hospital.